Senate Resolution 67
By: Senators Halpern of the 39th, Esteves of the 35th, Kirkpatrick of the 32nd, Rhett of the
33rd, Merritt of the 9th and others
ADOPTED SENATE
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 2, 2025, as Georgia Arts Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, arts and culture embody much of the accumulated wisdom, intellect, and
4 imagination of humankind; and
5 WHEREAS, arts and culture improve the overall quality of life in Georgia's communities;
6 and
7 WHEREAS, Georgians recognize the arts and culture industry as an important pillar and a
8 source of pride in their neighborhoods and communities; and
9 WHEREAS, towns, cities, and counties, through their local and state arts agencies and
10 councils representing thousands of arts and cultural organizations, celebrate the value and
11 importance of arts and culture in the lives of Georgians and the health of thriving
12 communities during Georgia Arts Day; and
13 WHEREAS, through organizational spending and the resulting economic impact, the arts and
14 culture industry generated $1.3 billion in 2022, supporting 19,734 Georgia jobs; and
